                <div id="commands">
                    <h4>Commands</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><code>/chester spawn (type)</code> - <i>Spawn a Chester</i></li>
                        <li><code>/chester add (slots/perkpoints) (amount) [player]</code> - <i>Add slots/perkpoints to
                                player</i></li>
                        <li><code>/chester reload</code> - <i>Reload settings</i></li>
                        <li><code>/chester delete [player]</code> - <i>Delete a Chester</i></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="permissions">
                    <h4>Permissions</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>chester.spawn."type" or chester.spawn.*</li>
                        <li>chester.add</li>
                        <li>chester.reload</li>
                        <li>chester.custom_name.color</li>
                        <li>chester.delete and chester.delete.other</li>
                        <li>chester.recipe."type" or chester.recipe.*</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="slots">
                    <h4>Slots</h4>
                    <img src="/img/slots.png"></img>
                    <p>Slots are spaces in Chester's inventory. Can be bought using <a
                            href="https://www.spigotmc.org/resources/vault.34315/" target="_blank">Vault</a> as
                        dependency or with the command: <code>/chester add slots (amount) [player]</code>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <info>(i) </info>Chester picks up loose objects on the floor, if he no longer has slots
                        available in the inventory, he will not be able to pick up anything else.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <info>(i) </info>The maximum number of slots that each type of Chester can have to can be
                        modified within its .yml <i>(types/<b>type</b>.yml)</i>.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div id="custom_name">
                    <h4>Custom name</h4>
                    <img src="/img/custom_name.png"></img>
                    <p>To rename our Chester, it is necessary to right-click it, open the profile menu and select the
                        item <strong>"Custon name"</strong>. When the menu closes, the new name must be written in the
                        chat.</p>
                    <p>
                        <info>(i) </info>To write the name in colors, we need to have the permission
                        'chester.custom_name.color'</i>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div id="statistics">
                    <h4>Statistics</h4>
                    <img src="/img/stats.png"></img>
                    <p>Chester brings statistics that allow him to keep track of what he was doing. Some of them are:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Distance traveled</li>
                        <li>Collected objects</li>
                        <li>Dropped objects</li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p>They can be viewed in the <i>Profile</i> menu by placing the cursor on the item
                        <i>Statistics</i>.</p>
                </div>
                <div id="perks">
                    <h4>Perks</h4>
                    <img src="/img/perks_inv.png"></img>

                    <p>Perks are improvements that can be assigned to our Chester, these can be purchased with
                        perkpoints, the plugin's
                        own currency.
                        <br /> Current types of perks include following:
                    <ul>
                        <li>ALL_RESISTANCE <i>(Damage reduced)</i></li>
                        <li>EXPLOSION_RESISTANCE <i>(Explosion damage is reduced)</i></li>
                        <li>FIRE_RESISTANCE <i>(Fire damage is reduced)</i></li>
                        <li>PROJECTILE_RESISTANCE <i>(Projectile damage is reduced)</i></li>
                        <li>SPEED <i>(Speed boost)</i></li>
                        <li>ITEM_FINDER <i>(Increase search radius)</i></li>
                        <li>ITEM_KEEPER <i>(Reduces loss of objects)</i></li>
                        <li>MAX_HEALTH <i>(Add max health)</i></li>
                        <li>REG_BOOST <i>(Add regeneration boost)</i></li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        <info>(i) </info>To customize a perk or create your own, enter the yml that you want to edit and
                        change any of
                        the following values:
